11/12/2006
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- KFOR personnel began destroying on Saturday (December 9th) illegal arms collected by the Kosovo Police Service in the past few weeks.
In all, some 1,200 weapons will be destroyed at the Victoria base.
KFOR says such disarmament operations will continue.
In other news, the office of UN special envoy Martti Ahtisaari issued a statement Sunday condemning any form of violence or terrorism in the province.
Senior Belgrade officials had criticised Ahtisaari for failing to denounce an explosion Friday along a train track near the eastern village of Mijalic.
The incident was blamed on ethnic Albanian extremists.
There were no injuries.
(Tanjug, Beta, RTS - 09/12/06)
